Basic course of organic chemistry, dealing with structure, naming and important reactions of organic compounds. This lecture course is accompanied by seminars.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Course gives an overview of basic organic chemistry, nomenclature of organic compound and their classification, and reactions and mechanisms of the traditional functional groups.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has completed the course: * recognizes the main classes of organic compounds, * understands the principles of naming of organic compounds and is able to apply them, * knows characteristic reactions of main classes of organic compounds and can explain their occurrence, * predicts the chemical and physical properties of an organic compound proceeding from structure of the molecule, * recognizes the important natural compounds: saccharides, peptides, nucleic acids and lipids
